data.name: ABITEC Corporation
data.description: ABITEC is passionate about creating premium ingredients and providing unparalleled technical support and service. With over 60 years experience in ester chemistry and manufacturing we source the highest quality raw materials and manufacture right here in the US. We have been solving the challenges of drug delivery for over 20 years and provide some of the most nutritionally beneficial, safe, and naturally sourced ingredients that exist in the market today. Beyond that, our quality control and agility ensures you always get the same quality product and you always get it when you need it.

data.name: Capmul
data.description: CAPMUL® multi-functional, high purity monoesters provide superior skin penetration and emolliency with excellent effects against microorganisms.  Certain grades of CAPMUL® may be used to inhibit the growth of gram positive and negative bacteria, yeast, and mold in many "preservative free" products. They are used to produce stable emulsions, to modify viscosity and they can act as carriers and vehicles in selected applications.

data.name: Captex
data.description: Captex® Medium-Chain Triglycerides originate from renewable vegetable-based sources (typically palm, palm kernel and/or coconut). These food-grade, safe, responsibly sourced ingredients are best known for their functional benefits as emulsifiers, solubilizers and refatting agents for use in a range of markets and applications including, personal care, cosmetics, food, and nutritional supplements. Additionally, these products boast numerous health benefits in areas such as weight management, energy, and cognition.ABITEC offers a variety of C8 (caprylic) and C10 (capric) variations to suite your formulation requirements.

data.name: Accoquat
data.description: ABITEC’s Accoquat line is quite versatile offering products for several industrial markets including, Car Rinse Aids, Fabric Softeners, and Household Industrial & Institutional.Our Accoquat Car Rinse Aid Emulsifiers offer improved performance, ease of use and versality.  We have a unique range of CS products, including high flash options and a dilute-and-shoot system that can accommodate all your formulation needs.Our Accoquat Fabric Softener quats are utilized in both consumer and industrial laundry applications. Our diamido amine quats are an excellent choice for commercial laundries where drying temperatures tend to be high and our imidazolinium quats provide the ultimate in softening and anti-static performance. And we offer high-flash products that meet DOT standards for non-flammability.

data.name: Caprol
data.description:
These polyglycerol esters (PGEs) function as EO-free surfactants and solubilizers in an array of applications because they offer a wide range of HLBs. In addition, they offer other benefits such as: improves texture and consistency,
works well to improve flow properties,
stabilizes aerated systems by controlling the agglomeration of fat globules, reduces interfacial tension at oil-water boundaries.

data.name: HydroKote
data.description: Hydro~Kote hydrogenated vegetable oils are refined, bleached, and deodorized. Their unique properties make them very useful in a variety of applications for the pharmaceutical industry. Their Applications Include: Topical creams and ointments, Suppositories, Controlled Release, Replacement to cocoa butter

data.name: Pureco
data.description: Pureco oils are highly-refined, bleached, and deodorized vegetable oils. ABITEC offers both hydrogenated and non-hydrogenated versions to provide melting and lubrication properties required for applications across many markets including pharmaceuticals, personal care, and industrial applications such as fiber glass.Their applications include Dietary Supplements Functional Foods, Oral Pharmaceuticals, Base Fluids and Fiber Glass

data.name: Acconon
data.description: Acconon products are well-characterized mixtures of polyoxyethylene mono- and diglycerides, fatty acids or fatty alcohols. In addition to functioning as excellent oil/water emulsifiers, many of these products can add emolliency to creams and lotions. Our line includes alkoxylates based on natural oils such as coconut, castor, and apricot oil.

data.name: BBS-C
data.description: BBS-C is an all-purpose, food-grade, partiallyhydrogenated vegetable oil (soybean and cottonseed) with bland flavor, good stability, superior creaming and resistance to oxidation.

data.name: Capmul® MCM
data.description: Capmul® MCM is a mono- and diglyceride with unique properties and versatility as a solvent, emulsifier, and emollient for creams, lotions, and rinse-off applications. This high purity distilled monoester is effective as a preservative alternative, based on natural materials, and makes an excellent primary or secondary surfactant in personal care products and cosmetics. It is used to produce stable emulsions, to modify viscosity and can act as a carrier and vehicle in selected applications. It is manufactured in USA.

data.description: Capmul® MCM C8 EP/NF is a mixture of monoacylglycerols, containing variable quantities of diand tri-acylglycerols, obtained by direct esterification of glycerol with caprylic (octanoic) acid. It is manufactured in USA.

summary.name: Certifications & Compliance

data.description: Acconon® MC8-2 EP/NF is a mixture of monoesters, diesters, and triesters of glycerol and monoesters and diesters of polyethylene glycols with a mean relative molecular weight between 200-400. It may contain free macrogols. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Caprol® PGE 860
data.description: Caprol® PGE 860 is a very unique product for ABITEC, with the highest HLB of our polyglycerol family. This ingredient is well-known for its slip & foam stabilizing capabilities in rinse off products such as 2-in-1 shampoos. It also provides improved hydration & moisture for healthier looking hair.   Additionally, this food-grade, bio-based ingredient is a premium plasticizer in any range of skincare products aiding in sealed moisture and reduction of dry and flaky skin. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Capmul® GMO-50 EP/NF
data.description: Capmul® GMO-50 EP/NF (Glyceryl Monooleate) is a mixture of monoglycerides, mainly glyceryl monooleate, together with variable quantities of diglycerides and triglycerides. The nominal content of monoglycerides is 60%. It is obtained by partial glycerolysis of vegetable oil that consists mainly of triglycerides of oleic acid, or by esterification of glycerol with oleic acid of vegetable origin. A suitable antioxidant may be added. Capmul® GMO-50 EP/NF is a multi-functional emulsifier useful in the production of pharmaceutical and food products. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Accoquat® CS-4000
data.description: Accoquat® CS-4000 is a unique blend of cationic emulsifiers in a blended solvent system especially designed for micro-emulsification of formulations of mineral seal oils (MSO) or other organic hydrophobes. It micro-emulsifies MSO effectively with ethylene glycol mono butyl ether as its coupling agent. Accoquat® CS-4000 can produce micro-emulsions with MSO from 10-30% MSO concentration, (depending on the properties of the MSO), however is most cost effective from 15-30% MSO concentrations. Accoquat® CS-4000 generally does not require additional emulsifiers or other nonionic surfactants to produce an easily dispersible and fine micro-emulsion for rapid beading and spreading. With substantially less emulsifier it is very cost effective for ultra-type drying aids. Upon dilution in water, its unique blend of chemistries provides a consistently-functioning, high-performance, very fine micro-emulsion with MSOs. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Accoquat® CS-5000
data.description: Accoquat® CS-5000 is a blend of cationic emulsifiers designed to produce micro-emulsions when combined with mineral seal oil (MSO). These micro-emulsions are most often used as the basis for car rinse-aids and other post-wash treatments in commercial and home applications. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Sterotex® K, NF

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Hardened soy oils, Hardened soybean oils, Hydrocote

data.description: Sterotex® K, NF is a powder that is widely used as a lubricant in tablet manufacturing in pharmaceutical industries. It may be used in compacting and compounding processes in the catalyst, ceramic and powder metallurgy fields. Sterotex® K, NF is derived from renewable vegetable oils that are fully refined, bleached, and deodorized and is a neutral organic ester (triglyceride) that is low in ash content. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Capmul® GMO-50
data.description: Capmul® GMO-50 glycerol monooleate is a food-grade multifunctional emulsifier that is highly useful in personal care & cosmetic applications such as, lotions, creams, lipsticks, and eyeliners. Capmul GMO-50 is sunflower glycerides and suitable in barrier creams and lotions. It easily forms gel phases with other surfactants in aqueous environments and can serve as a refatting agent. It is an excellent non polymeric invert emulsifier providing an elegant finish to your formulation. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 355
data.description: Captex® 355 Medium-Chain Triglycerides originate from vegetable-based sources (typically palm, palm kernel and/or coconut). These food-grade, safe, responsibly sourced ingredients are best known for their functional benefits as emulsifiers, solubilizers and refatting agents for use in a range of markets and applications. They are preferred lipophilic vehicles and solvents for use in various delivery systems, but are most well-known for their numerous health benefits in areas such as weight management, energy, and cognition.ABITEC offers a variety of C8 (caprylic) and C10 (capric) variations to suite your formulation requirements. It is manufactured in USA.

data.description: Captex® 355 EP/NF/JPE is manufactured by the esterification of glycerin and fatty acids, mainly caprylic (‰ˆ55%) and capric. It contains not less than 95% of saturated fatty acids with 8 and 10 carbon atoms. It is prepared from raw materials of vegetable sources. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 170 EP

summary.name: Certifications & Compliance
items: The Food Allergen Labeling & Consumer Protection Act of 2004 (FALCPA)

data.description: Captex® 170 EP is an ester prepared from the dehydration of coco fatty alcohols with caprylic and capric acids. It is a polar lipid suitable for solubilizing many types of active ingredients. It may also enhance translocation of API. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 8000
data.description: Captex® 8000 Medium-Chain Triglycerides originate from renewable vegetable-based sources (typically palm, palm kernel and/or coconut). Captex 8000 is comprised of pure C8 (caprylic) fatty acid, which are food-grade, safe, and responsibly sourced. They are best known for their functional benefits as emulsifiers, solubilizers and refatting agents for use in personal care and cosmetic applications, but also boast numerous health benefits in human nutrition such as weight management, energy, and cognition. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 300 EP/NF

summary.name: Certifications & Compliance
items: The Food Allergen Labeling & Consumer Protection Act of 2004 (FALCPA)

data.description: Captex® 300 EP/NF is manufactured by the esterification of glycerin and fatty acids, mainly caprylic (‰ˆ70%) and capric. It contains not less than 95% of saturated fatty acids with 8 and 10 carbon atoms. It is prepared from raw materials of vegetable sources. It is miscible with most organic solvents including 96% ethanol. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 300
data.description: Captex® 300 Medium-Chain Triglycerides originate from renewable vegetable-based sources (typically palm, palm kernel and/or coconut). This mix of C8 (caprylic) and C10 (capric) fatty acids are food-grade, safe, responsibly sourced ingredients. They are best known for their functional benefits as emulsifiers, solubilizers and refatting agents for use in personal care and cosmetic applications, but also boast numerous health benefits in areas such as weight management, energy, and cognition. This product contains about 70% C8 and 30% C10. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 100
data.description: Captex® 100 is a diester formed from a reaction of selected high-purity vegetable fatty acids and propylene glycol. It is Kosher certified. Captex® 100 is totally miscible in mineral oil and in 95% ethanol. It has a lower viscosity than mineral oil. Captex® 100 is an excellent skin emollient and produces a smooth, non-greasy, powdery after-feel with shine. Due to its excellent solvency, Captex® 100 works exceptionally well as a substitute for mineral oil in cosmetic makeup-remover formulas. Because of its unique properties, viscosity, and miscibility with other cosmetic components, Captex® 100 offers advantages in suncare and haircare products where spreadability and shine are desired. The non-oily character, excellent stability, bland taste, and neutral odor make this product an ideal choice as a solubilizer and carrier of vitamins, colors, and flavors for selected pharmaceutical and nutritional formulations, or processing aids such as pan and mold-release agents. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 170
data.description: Captex® 170 medium-chain triglyceride is a cocoyl caprylocaprate that is a low viscous liquid at room temperature, making it an excellent film former and plasticizer for cosmetic formulations. It is also an excellent emollient and skin feel modifier. Captex 170 is able to translocate actives across the skin with and not through it. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® GTO
data.description: Captex® GTO is a specialty triglyceride manufactured by the esterification of fractionated fatty acids (mainly oleic) and glycerin. Fully refined and deodorized, and with excellent stability, low irritation, bland taste and odor, Captex® GTO is ideally suited for a variety of nutritional and personal care applications. It is manufactured in USA.

data.description: Captex® 200P is propylene glycol diesters of saturated fatty acids, mainly of caprylic and capric acids of vegetable origin. The low viscosity, excellent lubricity, and relatively non-oily character of Captex® 200P makes it ideally suited for a variety of pharmaceutical and clinical nutritional applications, including microemulsions, soft-gelatin capsules, suspensions, and suppositories. It is manufactured in USA.

data.name: Captex® 200

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 1,2-Propanediol dioctanoate, 1,2-Propylene glycol dicaprylate, Propylene glycol dioctanoate

data.description: CAPTEX® 200 is a full-refined ester manufactured by the esterification of selected vegetable fatty acids (mainly caprylic and capric) with propylene glycol. It is miscible with most organic solvents including 95% ethanol. The low viscosity, excellent lubricity, low irritation, and the relatively non-oily character of CAPTEX® 200 makes it ideally suited for a variety of nutritional, personal care, and cosmetic applications. CAPTEX® 200 carries Kosher certification and has excellent stability. It is manufactured in USA.
